PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F446A1773191770
OL,3,CEx-partner tells court Natalie McNally
OL,4,Cdeath unrelated to phone reset
OL,6,FHer partner, Stephen McCullagh, 36, of
OL,7,FWoodland Gardens in Lisburn, is on
OL,8,Ftrial for her murder at Belfast Crown
OL,9,FCourt.
OL,11,FHe has denied the charge.
OL,13,FPreviously, McCullagh's trial has
OL,14,Fheard he told police that Ms McNally's
OL,15,Fex had been responsible.
OL,17,FThe man responded saying that was
OL,18,F"ridiculous" when that was put to him
OL,19,Fin court on Monday.
OL,26,@zD@AOUzD@LO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/10
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,447,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F446A1773191770
OL,3,CEx-partner tells court Natalie McNally
OL,4,Cdeath unrelated to phone reset
OL,6,FHe described Ms McNally as his best
OL,7,Ffriend, and insisted that McCullagh
OL,8,Fwas responsible for her death.
OL,10,FA jury of six men and six women has
OL,11,Fbeen sworn in to serve during the
OL,12,Ftrial, which is expected to last about
OL,13,Ffive weeks, before Mr Justice Patrick
OL,14,FKinney.
OL,16,FMs McNally's family and friends have
OL,17,Fbeen watching on from the public
OL,18,Fgallery during the trial.
OL,20,FThe former partner returned to
OL,21,Fcontinue his evidence on Tuesday.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/10
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,447,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F446A1773191770
OL,3,CEx-partner tells court Natalie McNally
OL,4,Cdeath unrelated to phone reset
OL,6,FThe court heard that he had been
OL,7,Farrested within the last two weeks and
OL,8,Fwas on probation after being accused
OL,9,Fof sending threatening messages to a
OL,10,Fman that a former partner of his had
OL,11,Fbeen involved with.
OL,13,FHe was reminded several times during
OL,14,Fhis evidence of his right not to
OL,15,Fanswer a question if he risked self-
OL,16,Fincrimination.
OL,18,F"I know, I don't care, I'm here to
OL,19,Ftell the truth for Natalie, and that's
OL,20,Fwhat I'm going to do," he said.
OL,26,@zD@AOU|D@VO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/10
